        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-07-11T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-07-11T02:00:00-05:00" n="94"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <head>94. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Cuba</gloss> to the <gloss
                        type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d94fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 737.56/7–1158. Secret; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Havana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-07-11T02:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1958—2 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>49. For <persName corresp="#p_SWP1">Snow</persName>
                    <gloss target="#t_ARA1">ARA</gloss>. During conference with <persName
                        corresp="#p_BZF1">Batista</persName> July 10 he stated he understood US
                    suspension of shipment of combat arms and our desire for non-involvement in
                    Cuban internal affairs. However, he was deeply concerned over what <gloss
                        target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> considers as US intervention in Cuban affairs.
                    He has been informed by his Ambassadors in England and Canada that these nations
                    declined to sell arms to Cuba because US allegedly refused to give clearance. He
                    added that if <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> does not receive arms it could
                    bring about overthrow of Cuban Government.</p>
                <p>I said I was unaware of the foregoing and would advise my government of his
                    concern.</p>
                <p>Request information concerning validity of above.<note n="2" xml:id="d94fn2">See
                            <ref target="#d102fn3">footnote 3, Document 102</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SEET1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
